Tell GitHub to ignore Unity asset and metadata files when calculating language percentage.
This ensures your project is correctly identified as C# (C-Sharp).
Ignore all .meta files (Unity's YAML metadata)
*.meta linguist-generated=true

Ignore .unity (scene) files
*.unity linguist-generated=true

Ignore .asset and .prefab files
*.asset linguist-generated=true
*.prefab linguist-generated=true

Ignore .controller files (Animator/Mecanim data)
*.controller linguist-generated=true

Explicitly mark C# as the language for .cs files (usually redundant but safe)
*.cs linguist-language=C#
